The paper discusses the origin and evolution of natural languages, which is a topic closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also focuses on planning agents, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of abstractions in language construction, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
